#. type: Title ====
#: _versions/main/guides/resteasy-reactive-migration.adoc
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Service Loading"
msgstr "жӯЈеңЁеҠ иҪҪжңҚеҠЎ"

#: _versions/main/guides/resteasy-reactive-migration.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"RESTEasy Classic supports determining providers at build time using Java's Service Loader. In order to ensure that all providers are determined at build time,\n"
"RESTEasy Reactive does not support this feature. Instead, users that have providers in application dependencies are encouraged to index those dependencies\n"
"using one of the methods described in the xref:cdi-reference.adoc#bean_discovery[Bean Discovery] section of the CDI guide."
msgstr "RESTEasy Classic ж”ҜжҢҒдҪҝз”Ё Java зҡ„жңҚеҠЎеҠ иҪҪеҷЁпјҲService LoaderпјүеңЁжһ„е»әж—¶зЎ®е®ҡжҸҗдҫӣиҖ…гҖӮдёәдәҶзЎ®дҝқеңЁжһ„е»әж—¶зЎ®е®ҡжүҖжңүжҸҗдҫӣзЁӢеәҸпјҢRESTEasy Reactive дёҚж”ҜжҢҒиҜҘеҠҹиғҪгҖӮзӣёеҸҚпјҢжҲ‘д»¬йј“еҠұеңЁеә”з”ЁзЁӢеәҸдҫқиө–е…ізі»дёӯжңүжҸҗдҫӣиҖ…зҡ„з”ЁжҲ·дҪҝз”Ё CDI жҢҮеҚ—дёӯ xref:cdi-reference.adoc#bean_discovery[Bean Discovery] йғЁеҲҶжҸҸиҝ°зҡ„ж–№жі•д№ӢдёҖдёәиҝҷдәӣдҫқиө–е…ізі»е»әз«Ӣзҙўеј•гҖӮ"

#. type: Title ===
#: _versions/main/guides/resteasy-reactive-migration.adoc
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Multipart support"
msgstr "еӨҡйғЁеҲҶж”ҜжҢҒ"

#: _versions/main/guides/resteasy-reactive-migration.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "HTTP Multipart support in RESTEasy Reactive does **not** reuse the same types or annotations as RESTEasy Classic and thus users are encouraged to read <<resteasy-reactive#multipart,this>> part of the reference documentation."
msgstr "RESTEasy Reactive дёӯзҡ„ HTTP Multipart ж”ҜжҢҒ *жІЎжңү* йҮҚеӨҚдҪҝз”ЁдёҺ RESTEasy Classic зӣёеҗҢзҡ„зұ»еһӢжҲ–жіЁи§ЈпјҢеӣ жӯӨе»әи®®з”ЁжҲ·йҳ…иҜ» xref:resteasy-reactive.adoc#multipart[иҝҷйғЁеҲҶ] еҸӮиҖғж–ҮжЎЈгҖӮ"

#: _versions/main/guides/resteasy-reactive-migration.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Users migrating multipart resources to RESTEasy Reactive should be aware of the configuration parameter `quarkus.http.limits.max-form-attribute-size`, as this poses an upper limit to the size of each part.\n"
"Any request with a part size exceeding this configuration value will result in HTTP status code 413."
msgstr "е°ҶеӨҡйғЁеҲҶиө„жәҗиҝҒз§»еҲ° RESTEasy Reactive зҡ„з”ЁжҲ·еә”жіЁж„Ҹй…ҚзҪ®еҸӮж•° `quarkus.http.limits.max-form-attribute-size` пјҢеӣ дёәиҝҷжҳҜеҜ№жҜҸдёӘйғЁеҲҶеӨ§е°Ҹзҡ„дёҠйҷҗгҖӮд»»дҪ•йғЁеҲҶеӨ§е°Ҹи¶…иҝҮиҜҘй…ҚзҪ®еҖјзҡ„иҜ·жұӮйғҪе°ҶеҜјиҮҙ HTTP зҠ¶жҖҒд»Јз Ғ 413гҖӮ"

#. type: Title ===
#: _versions/main/guides/resteasy-reactive-migration.adoc
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Default media types"
msgstr "й»ҳи®ӨеӘ’дҪ“зұ»еһӢ"

#: _versions/main/guides/resteasy-reactive-migration.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Quarkus uses smart defaults when determining the media type of Jakarta REST methods in order to simplify common use cases.\n"
"The difference between `quarkus-resteasy-reactive` and `quarkus-resteasy` is the use of `text/plain` as the default media type instead of `text/html`\n"
"when the method returns a `String`."
msgstr "еңЁзЎ®е®ҡ Jakarta REST ж–№жі•зҡ„еӘ’дҪ“зұ»еһӢж—¶пјҢQuarkus дҪҝз”ЁдәҶжҷәиғҪй»ҳи®ӨеҖјпјҢд»Ҙз®ҖеҢ–еёёи§Ғз”ЁдҫӢгҖӮ `quarkus-resteasy-reactive` е’Ң `quarkus-resteasy` зҡ„еҢәеҲ«еңЁдәҺпјҢеҪ“ж–№жі•иҝ”еӣһ `String` ж—¶пјҢдҪҝз”Ё `text/plain` дҪңдёәй»ҳи®ӨеӘ’дҪ“зұ»еһӢпјҢиҖҢдёҚжҳҜ `text/html` гҖӮ"

#: _versions/main/guides/resteasy-reactive-migration.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Injection of `@SessionScoped` beans"
msgstr "`@SessionScoped` иҢғеӣҙзҡ„ Bean зҡ„жіЁе…Ҙ"

#: _versions/main/guides/resteasy-reactive-migration.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "`@SessionScoped` beans are currently not supported. Should you really need this functionality, you'll need to use RESTEasy Classic instead of RESTEasy Reactive."
msgstr "зӣ®еүҚдёҚж”ҜжҢҒ `@SessionScoped иҢғеӣҙзҡ„` BeanгҖӮеҰӮжһңжӮЁзЎ®е®һйңҖиҰҒжӯӨеҠҹиғҪпјҢеҲҷйңҖиҰҒдҪҝз”Ё RESTEasy Classic иҖҢдёҚжҳҜ RESTEasy ReactiveгҖӮ"

#. type: Title ===
#: _versions/main/guides/resteasy-reactive-migration.adoc
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Servlets"
msgstr "Servlet"

#: _versions/main/guides/resteasy-reactive-migration.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"RESTEasy Reactive does **not** support servlets.\n"
"If your project depends on servlets you have to migrate them.\n"
"A servlet-based JAX-RS implementation must support injections of these types with the `@Context` annotation: `ServletConfig`, `ServletContext`, `HttpServletRequest` and `HttpServletResponse`.\n"
"Since RESTEasy Reactive is not servlet-based these injections will not work."
msgstr "RESTEasy Reactive *дёҚ* ж”ҜжҢҒ servletsгҖӮеҰӮжһңжӮЁзҡ„йЎ№зӣ®дҫқиө–дәҺ servletпјҢжӮЁеҝ…йЎ»иҝҒз§»е®ғд»¬гҖӮеҹәдәҺ servlet зҡ„ JAX-RS е®һзҺ°еҝ…йЎ»йҖҡиҝҮ `@Context` жіЁи§Јж”ҜжҢҒиҝҷдәӣзұ»еһӢзҡ„жіЁе…Ҙпјҡ `ServletConfig` , `ServletContext` , `HttpServletRequest` е’Ң `HttpServletResponse` гҖӮз”ұдәҺ RESTEasy Reactive дёҚжҳҜеҹәдәҺ servlet зҡ„пјҢеӣ жӯӨиҝҷдәӣжіЁе…Ҙе°ҶдёҚиө·дҪңз”ЁгҖӮ"

#: _versions/main/guides/resteasy-reactive-migration.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"It is not always obvious that this will fail especially if you depend on an extension like `quarkus-undertow` which supplies the interfaces.\n"
"For example, if you write this you could compile it but get an exception on calling it:"
